HEADWORD: Oleraceous
<hw>Ol`er*a"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>oleraceus</ets>, from <ets>olus</ets>, <ets>oleris</ets>, garden or
pot herbs, vegetables.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to pot herbs; of the
nature or having the qualities of herbs for cookery; esculent.</def>
<rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
